commit.message:
Expose keyed Blake2 interface

This fixes haskell-crypto/cryptonite#196.

 - FFI: expose keyed init functions for all Blake2 variants
 - Add HashBlake2 typeclass in Crypto.Hash.Blake2 to support keyed init
 - Add KeyedBlake2 module to Crypto.MAC

Uses KAT vectors from BLAKE2/BLAKE2 repository, plus quickcheck tests
analogous to those in the KAT_KMAC test module.

Strict `byteArray` of `IV c`

This provides a way to seq `IV c` and its content when client wants to
prevent thunk exploding, It's not rare to apply multiple `ivAdd` on
single `IV c` and we often don't want thunk here.

commit.message:
README.md: Remove wrong statement about LTS presence

Closes #11:

>  Each versions of stackage (going back 3 stable LTS) has a crypton version 

This isn't true. I checked and the first crypton release is in LTS 21.
LTS 3 - 20 have a release of cryptonite. (LTS 21 has both crypton and cryptonite.)
